post_text:
Mr. Clarke‚Äôs "Tournament of Historical Significance" project looked a little different this year, but it was still a fun and engaging learning opportunity for our 7th Grade Social Studies students!

Typically, 7th graders choose their top-32 historical figures in U.S. History, each student then picks one historical figure, and then they go through a March Madness-styled tournament in which students debate against one another with the winner moving on from round to round.

Prior to the closure, students established their top-32 but were unable to do the debate-formatted tournament. The tournament still took place, though, through student-led research and a vote on who they thought was most historically significant in each matchup.

Check out the final brackets with the winners!

post_text: 3/30/20 - Central 51 Parent Update
text:
3/30/20 - Central 51 Parent Update

CENTRAL51.NET
3/30/20 - Central 51 Parent Update

post_text:
*Reminder*

Curbside Chromebook pickup for 4th through 8th grade students will be tomorrow (Tuesday, March 31st) from 10:30 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. at the Central Intermediate School main office entry. Staff will be available to bring Chromebooks to vehicles.

Please complete the following two steps if you would like to pick up a(n) Chromebook(s).

- Complete the Google Form linked below by Monday, March 30th at 5:00 p.m. This will give staff an adequate amount of time to ensure Chromebooks are ready for pickup.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeWxKxStPaI5-LDMsrWrdEcbywDEB9mfiY0SXY8aCMEgKmWiQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

- Log into Skyward Family Access and update the Chromebook Use (Parent) form for each child by tonight (Monday, March 30th) at 5:00 p.m. See the video linked below for directions on how to update the Chromebook Use (Parent) form.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2TA1IykdKac&feature=youtu.be

If you are unable to pick up the Chromebook during this time, please contact Mrs. Bush, assistant principal, at ebush@central51.net.

post_text:
The Snow White Variety Show
Directed by Sarah Whoolard
Assisted by Lynn Randolph
Friday, March 6th @ 7pm - CPS Gym
Saturday, March 7th @ 2pm - CPS Gym

CIS Drama proudly presents, The Snow White Variety Hour.

Be a part of the studio audience of Real Talk with Fairytale Legends, where the seven dwarves tell the story of Snow White as the Fairytale Players bring it to life. Each dwarf takes a turn telling part of Snow White‚Äôs famous story in his or her own unique voice. At any given moment, the story can be anything ‚Äî romance, comedy, home improvement show, suspense, Western, epic poetry, mystery, cooking show, stand-up routine, or blockbuster action movie! There‚Äôs even a ‚ÄúMiss Fairest of Them All‚Äù beauty pageant! It all culminates in a mad-dash ending of fast-changing genres that sets the record straight on Snow White‚Äôs happily-ever-after.

CIS hosted its first ever CIS Parents Cafe on Thursday, November 14th. In an effort to gain feedback from an even larger number of parents, we are asking that you please complete this CIS Parent Feedback Form. Your responses will help guide us as we continuously improve areas like curriculum, Social Emotional Learning, communication, and collaboration at Central Intermediate School.

Thank you!
